description: Run training and other long-running jobs in tmux
alwaysApply: true
---

# Use tmux for long-running jobs

- Always start training, inference services, preprocessing, downloads, and other long-running commands in a named tmux session.
- Before launching, check existing tmux sessions and running processes to avoid duplicates.
- Use a descriptive session name related to the experiment.
- After launching, inspect the tmux output and verify that the job reached a healthy running state.
- Tell the user the session name and the `tmux attach -t <session>` command.
- Short checks, tests, and one-off commands do not require tmux.
